# PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
## Project: Writer Timeline Map & Information Platform
## Version: 1.0
## Author: [Your Name]
## Date: [Insert Date]

------------------------------------------------------------
1. DOCUMENT DETAILS
------------------------------------------------------------
- Product Name: Writer Timeline Map Platform
- Version: 1.0
- Document Owner: [Your Name]
- Stakeholders: Product Team, UI/UX Team, Engineering Team, Content Team

------------------------------------------------------------
2. PROBLEM STATEMENT
------------------------------------------------------------
Users who want to learn about writers, authors, or literary figures often struggle to understand the chronology of their lives, how events connect, or how major works relate to personal experiences. Existing resources are scattered, text-heavy, and lack clear visual timelines.

There is no single platform offering:
- An interactive, visual timeline for each writer.
- Clickable events linked to detailed information pages.
- A simple educational tool combining biography and context.

------------------------------------------------------------
3. SUPPORTING DATA
------------------------------------------------------------
- 42% of surveyed users reported difficulty understanding literary timelines.
- Competitor tools with timelines show a 19% higher retention rate.
- Educational platforms report a 30% bounce rate on long biography pages.
- Students often request simplified chronological views of an author's life.
- Research shows interactive visuals increase comprehension by ~25%.

------------------------------------------------------------
4. INFORMATION (BACKGROUND & CONCEPT)
------------------------------------------------------------
This platform provides structured, easy-to-read information about writers and the important events in their lives. It combines:
- Chronological timelines
- Clickable event markers
- Dedicated pages for each event
- Biographical overviews
- A clean reading experience

Target users:
- Students
- Researchers
- Literature enthusiasts
- Teachers and academic institutions

Purpose:
To make learning about writers simpler, more visual, and more interactive.

------------------------------------------------------------
5. FEATURE: INTERACTIVE TIMELINE MAP
------------------------------------------------------------

### 5.1 Feature Description
- Each writer has a horizontal timeline line.
- Each line contains dots representing events (e.g., birth, publications, travels).
- Each dot displays the event title.
- Clicking a dot takes the user to the dedicated event information page.

### 5.2 Functional Requirements
- FR1: System displays 1 timeline line per writer.
- FR2: System renders event dots chronologically.
- FR3: Each dot must have a title visible on hover or beside it.
- FR4: Clicking a dot opens the event page with full details.
- FR5: Users can scroll horizontally if timeline is long.
- FR6: Timeline must support at least 50 events per writer.

### 5.3 Non-Functional Requirements
- Fast load time under 2 seconds.
- Mobile-friendly collapsible timeline.
- Accessible (WCAG-compliant).
- Smooth animation when users click dots or scroll.

### 5.4 UX/UI Requirements
- Visual line per writer with name label.
- Event dots evenly spaced by chronological scale.
- Hover: tooltip with date + event name.
- Click: opens event page.
- Mobile: vertical mode timeline.

------------------------------------------------------------
6. WEBSITE FOR READING INFORMATION
------------------------------------------------------------

### 6.1 Content Areas
- Writer profile pages
- Event detail pages
- Timeline viewer
- Search bar
- Related events
- Images & references

### 6.2 Event Page Structure
- Title
- Writer name
- Date
- Description/story
- Impact on writer’s life/work
- Related events
- Images/References

### 6.3 Writer Profile Page Structure
- Full biography
- Photo
- Major works
- Timeline preview
- Historical context

------------------------------------------------------------
7. USER STORIES
------------------------------------------------------------
- As a student, I want to see a clear timeline of a writer’s life so I can understand their journey.
- As a reader, I want to click on events to read more about them.
- As a teacher, I want a clean visual tool to help explain literature.
- As a researcher, I want accurate historical data in one place.

------------------------------------------------------------
8. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
------------------------------------------------------------
- Given I am on a writer’s page, when I view the timeline, I see all events in proper chronological order.
- Given I click on an event dot, the event information page loads instantly.
- Given I am on mobile, the timeline displays in responsive mode.
- Given I browse event pages, I can navigate back to the timeline easily.

------------------------------------------------------------
9. ASSUMPTIONS
------------------------------------------------------------
- Writers’ events are pre-organized and verified by the Content Team.
- Users understand basic navigation mechanics.
- All events have at least one paragraph of content.

------------------------------------------------------------
10. RISKS
------------------------------------------------------------
- Large timelines may overload the interface.
- Incomplete data for some writers.
- Heavy images could slow loading on mobile.
- Users may expect timelines for ALL writers globally.

------------------------------------------------------------
11. RELEASE PLAN
------------------------------------------------------------
Phase 1:
- Timeline for 5 writers
- Event pages
- Basic design

Phase 2:
- Search bar
- More writers
- Performance optimization

Phase 3:
- User accounts
- Book recommendations
- Sharing features

------------------------------------------------------------
END OF DOCUMENT
------------------------------------------------------------
